headline.print_headline: California Bill Would Increase Penalties for Soliciting Minors for Sex
headline.main: California Bill Would Increase Penalties for Soliciting Minors for Sex

lead_paragraph: Adults convicted of soliciting underage prostitutes for sex will spend a minimum of two days in jail and face fines of up to $10,000 under a bill passed by the California legislature on Thursday.
